A vintage 1970s technical illustration style depicting a powerful red wild boar (representing JBoss) leaping dynamically over a maze of interconnected server racks and circuit pathways, rendered in warm amber, burnt orange, and deep burgundy tones with halftone dot patterns and aged paper texture. The boar appears energetic and confident, mid-jump, with stylized motion lines trailing behind it. Below, a complex but organized network of geometric shapes suggests enterprise architecture and deployment pipelines. The composition has the aesthetic of a retro computer science textbook cover or vintage technical manual, with slightly faded colors and subtle grain throughout.
